## 🔴 Root Cause of Graphics Driver Gear Crash

The crash had **three layers**, each making it worse:

### Layer 1: `DefaultVersion.DXVK` static initializer crash
**File**: [DefaultVersion.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/DefaultVersion.java)

```java
// BEFORE (crashes on class load!)
public static final String DXVK = GPUInformation.getRenderer(null, null).contains("Mali") ? "1.10.3" : "2.3.1";
```

This executes as a **static class initializer** — the moment ANY [DefaultVersion](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/DefaultVersion.java#5-28) constant is referenced, it calls a JNI native method. If the native method returns `null` → NPE. If the library fails to load → `UnsatisfiedLinkError`. Since `DefaultVersion.WRAPPER_ADRENO` is referenced in [GraphicsDriverConfigDialog](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/contentdialog/GraphicsDriverConfigDialog.java#35-474), loading the dialog class triggers this crash first.

**Fix**: Wrapped in a safe method with `Throwable` catch.

### Layer 2: JNI `Error` subclasses bypass `catch (Exception e)`
**File**: [GPUInformation.java](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/GPUInformation.java)

All exception handling used `catch (Exception e)` but JNI failures throw:
- `UnsatisfiedLinkError` (extends `Error`, NOT `Exception`)
- `ExceptionInInitializerError` (extends `Error`)
- `NoClassDefFoundError` (extends `Error`)

These all **bypass** `catch (Exception e)` blocks → uncaught → Activity destroyed → user sent back.

**Fix**: 
- Rewrote [GPUInformation](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/GPUInformation.java#5-33) with safe wrappers ([getRendererSafe](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/GPUInformation.java#29-42), [enumerateExtensionsSafe](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/GPUInformation.java#43-56)) that catch `Throwable`
- Added `nativeLibLoaded` flag so methods return safe defaults if library fails to load
- Changed ALL catch blocks in dialog code to `Throwable`

### Layer 3: Null returns from JNI methods
[getRenderer()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/GPUInformation.java#23-26) can return `null`, but [isAdrenoGPU()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/GPUInformation.java#11-15) calls [getRenderer(null, context).toLowerCase()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/GPUInformation.java#23-26) — NPE chain.
[enumerateExtensions()](file:///home/max/Build/Emulator/WinNative/app/src/main/java/com/winlator/cmod/core/GPUInformation.java#27-28) can return `null` → `MultiSelectionComboBox.setItems(null)` → NPE on `items.length`.

**Fix**: Safe wrappers always return non-null defaults.

